==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crystallite
<hw>Crys"tal*lite</hw> <pr>(kr?s"t<it>a</it>l-l?t)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[See <er>Crystal</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A minute
mineral form like those common in glassy volcanic rocks and some slags,
not having a definite crystalline outline and not referable to any
mineral species, but marking the first step in the crystallization
process. According to their form crystallites are called
<stype>trichites</stype>, <stype>belonites</stype>,
<stype>globulites</stype>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 353 --></p>

<p><ent>Crystallizable</ent>⟦br⟧
